<H2 class=3Dtop>Additional Modes of Operation for Symmetric =
Algorithms</H2>
<H3>XTS-AES</H3>
<P>Currently, there exist multiple modes of operation that are described =
in the=20
NIST Special Publication 800-38 series. Most of these modes of operation =
are=20
message authentication codes and therefore have been listed under the =
MAC=20
section. XTS-AES is more like the original modes of operation and =
therefore is=20
described below.</P>
<UL class=3Dbullets1>
  <LI><A class=3Dpdf=20
  =
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/nistpubs/800-38E/nist-sp-800-38=
E.pdf"=20
  target=3D_blank>NIST SP 800-38E</A>, <EM>Recommendation for Block =
Cipher Modes=20
  of Operation: The XTS-AES Mode for Confidentiality on Block-Oriented =
Storage=20
  Devices</EM>, specifies the XTS-AES algorithm. </LI></UL>
<H3>Testing Requirements:</H3>
<P>Validation testing for XTS-AES mode of operation algorithm is handled =
by the=20
Cryptographic Algorithm Validation Program's (<A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/index.html">CAVP</A>) <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/testing_labs/index.html">CST =
labs</A>.</P>
<UL class=3Dbullets1>
  <LI>XTS-AES tests are described in <A class=3Dpdf=20
  href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/aes/XTSVS.pdf"=20
  target=3D_blank>The XTS-AES Validation System (XTSVS)</A>. </LI></UL>
<H3>Validation List:</H3>
<P>NIST maintains the current XTS-AES Validations. XTS-AES validations =
are=20
included on the <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/aes/aesval.html"=20
target=3D_blank>AES Validation List</A>. </P>
<H3>Other Information:</H3>
