<H2><A id=3D03 name=3D03></A>Secure Hash Standard (SHS)</H2>
<H3>(SHA-1, SHA-224, SHA-256, SHA-384, SHA-512, SHA-512/224 and =
SHA-512/256=20
algorithms)</H3>
<P>The <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/ST/toolkit/secure_hashing.html">Secur=
e Hash=20
Algorithms</A> (SHA-1, SHA-224, SHA-256, SHA-384, SHA-512, SHA-512/224 =
and=20
SHA-512/256) are specified in <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips180-4/fips-180-4.pdf" =

target=3D_blank>FIPS 180-4 dated March 2012</A>, <EM>Secure Hash =
Standard=20
(SHS)</EM>.</P>
<H3>Testing Requirements:</H3>
<P><A =
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/testing_labs/index.html">CST=20
labs</A> can test for conformance to the SHA algorithms in FIPS 180-4. =
The=20
testing requirements for these algorithms can be found in the document =
titled <A=20
class=3Dpdf =
