<H2>SP 800-108 Key Derivation Using Pseudorandom Functions - Key-Based - =
(KBKDF)=20
</H2>
<P><A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/nistpubs/800-108/sp800-108.pdf"=
=20
target=3D_blank>SP 800-108</A> dated October 2009, Recommendation for =
Key=20
Derivation Using Pseudorandom Functions specifies techniques for the =
derivation=20
of additional keying material from a secret key, either established =
through a=20
key establishment scheme or shared through some other manner, using =
pseudorandom=20
functions. </P>
<H3>Testing Requirements:</H3>
<P>CST labs can test for conformance to the Key-based Key Derivation =
Functions=20
(KBKDF) specified in Special Publication 800-108. The testing =
requirements for=20
this algorithm can be found in the document titled <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/KBKDF800-108/kbkdf=
vs.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>The SP800-108 Key Derivation Function Validation System=20
(KBKDFVS).</A>.</P>
<P><STRONG>Additional testing note:</STRONG> The KBKDF validation =
process=20
requires additional prerequisite testing of the underlying CMAC and/or =
HMAC=20
algorithm based on which MAC algorithm is supported and, the underlying=20
algorithm used to generate the key derivation key (SP800-56A KAS, =
SP800-90A=20
DRBG, and/or RNG). (See CAVP FAQ GEN.5 for more detailed information on=20
prerequisites.) </P>
<H3>Validation List:</H3>
<P>NIST maintains the current <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/KBKDF800-108/kbkdf=
val.htm"=20
target=3D_blank>SP800-108 KBKDF Validation List. </A>. </P>
<H3>Test Vectors:</H3>
<P>KBKDF Test Vectors - These files provide an electronic version of the =
test=20
vectors that can be used to informally verify the correctness of Key =
Derivation=20
Functions (KDF) using Counter Mode, Feedback Mode, and/or =
Double-Pipeline=20
Iteration Mode via the validation testing described in the KBKDFVS.=20
<EM><STRONG>However, use of these vectors does not take the place of =
validation=20
obtained through the Cryptographic Algorithm Validation Program=20
(CAVP).</STRONG></EM></P>
<P>Test Vectors for SP 800-108 KDFs See the KBKDFVS document for an =
explanation=20
of the files.</P>
<P><A class=3Dzip=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/KBKDF800-108/Count=
erMode.zip"=20
target=3D_parent>KDF in Counter Mode Test Vectors</A></P>
<P><A class=3Dzip=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/KBKDF800-108/Feedb=
ackModenocounter.zip"=20
target=3D_parent>KDF in Feedback Mode Test Vectors where no counter is=20
used</A></P>
<P><A class=3Dzip=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/KBKDF800-108/Feedb=
ackModewzeroiv.zip"=20
target=3D_parent>KDF in Feedback Mode Test Vectors where zero length IV =
