<H3>FIPS 186-3 ECDSA Signature Generation Component Testing</H3>
<P>This component test assumes the IUT requires hash sized messages as =
input to=20
the Signature Generation function. This validation test was designed for =

applications like the PIV card.</P>
<H3>Testing Requirements:</H3>
<P>Validation testing for FIPS 186-3 ECDSA Signature Generation =
component=20
testing is handled by the Cryptographic Algorithm Validation Program's =
(<A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/index.html">CAVP</A>) <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/testing_labs/index.html">CST =
labs</A>.=20
</P>
<UL class=3Dbullets1>
  <LI>FIPS 186-3 ECDSA Signature Generation component testing is the =
same as=20
  ECDSA Signature Generation tests except the length of the input =
message is the=20
  length of the hash value supported. Please see the Signature =
Generation tests=20
  described in <A class=3Dpdf=20
  =
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/dss2/ecdsa2vs.pdf"=
=20
  target=3D_blank>The Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm =
Validation System=20
