<H2>Retired Validation Testing</H2>
<H3>Data Encryption Standard (DES)</H3>
<P>FIPS 46-3, Data Encryption Standard (DES), was withdrawn May 19, 2005 =
because=20
the cryptographic algorithm no longer provided the security that is =
needed to=20
protect Federal government information. DES is no longer an Approved =
algorithm.=20
The DES Algorithm Validation Webpage is still accessible via the =
Validations=20
List webpage, for historical purposes only.</P>
<H3>Data (Message) Authentication Code (MAC) and Key Management Using =
ANSI=20
X9.17</H3>
<P>The automated conformance tests for FIPS 113 and 171 are no longer=20
operational. Currently, if a FIPS 140-1 or FIPS 140-2 cryptographic =
module=20
implements either of these two standards, the <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/testing_labs/index.html">CST =
testing=20
laboratories</A> perform some testing that these FIPS requirements are=20
implemented correctly in the cryptographic module.</P>
<H3>Message Authentication Code (MAC), FIPS 113</H3>
<P>The MAC Validation System (MVS) tested for compliance with <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips113/fips113.html"=20
target=3D_blank>FIPS 113</A>, Computer Data Authentication. A list of <A =

href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/des/mvsval.htm"=20
target=3D_blank>validated products</A> is maintained by the Security =
Technology=20
Group.</P>
<H3>Key Management Using ANSI X9.17, FIPS 171</H3>
<P>The Key Management Validation System (KMVS) tested for compliance =
with FIPS=20
171, Key Management Using ANSI X9.17. A list of <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cavp/documents/des/kmvsval.htm">v=
alidated=20
products</A> is maintained by the Security Technology=20
Group.</P><BR></DIV></DIV></DIV><!-- PAGE FOOTER STARTS HERE: INFO, =
